'''Assarting''' is the act of  ed lands for use in  or other purposes. In , it was illegal to assart any part of a . This was the greatest  that could be committed in a forest, being more than a waste: for whereas waste of the forest involves  trees and other shrubbery, this vegetation can grow again; assarting involves completely rooting up all trees &mdash; the total  of the forested area.
The term "assart" was also used for a parcel of land assarted. '''Assart rents''' were those paid to the British  for the forest lands assarted.
Many French places called  refer to that practice.